Mitsubishi Semiconductor AmericaInc, a subsdiary of &lt;Mitsubishi Electric Corp>, said it plansto invest  36 mln dlrs to expand its Durham, N.C. semiconductoroperation.    The company said it will build a building adjacent to thecompany's memory chip assembly plant and test center in N.C.The expansion will allow the subsidiary to fabricate thesilicon wafers used in producing Application SpecificIntegrated Circuits (ASIC) chips, the company said.    Construction is expected to begin in July, with operationsplanned to start in early 1988, the company added. Reuter&#3;